290
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:52,197
Oh, what happened to your ear?

291
00:24:52,920 --> 00:24:54,194
Did you get in a fight?

292
00:24:56,880 --> 00:24:59,235
I'm real sorry, sweetie,
but Dr. Henry won't be in until Monday.

293
00:24:59,360 --> 00:25:02,158
He and his family have gone to Branson.
They got a timeshare condo there.

294
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:04,589
Well, it looks infected to me.

295
00:25:05,240 --> 00:25:07,037
You could take her over to Little Rock.

296
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:10,233
Well, can I just bring her in
first thing Monday morning?

297
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:11,958
Sure, you can.
Now what's her name?

298
00:25:12,080 --> 00:25:13,752
She doesn't have one.
I just found her.

299
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:16,713
Well, I gotta have something
put down in the appointment book.

300
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:19,629
Bessie.

301
00:25:20,880 --> 00:25:22,279
Do you maybe have
some ointment or something?

302
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:24,152
Yeah, I think I got
a sample here somewhere.

303
00:25:25,640 --> 00:25:27,278
- Oh, here you go.
- Thanks.

304
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:30,119
Oh, she sure is a cutie.
We'll see you Monday.

305
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:33,198
Is it true that when
you take 'em to the pound,

306
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:34,594
they put 'em to sleep after a week?

307
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:36,358
Yes, ma'am, they sure do.

308
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:45,792
So what's up with your face?

309
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:47,433
Nothing. It's stupid.

310
00:25:47,560 --> 00:25:49,755
- Did you get a puppy?
- No, I found a stray.

311
00:25:49,920 --> 00:25:50,796
Keeping it?

312
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:53,431
Taking it to the pound on Monday.

313
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:55,634
Big eater, huh?

314
00:26:01,520 --> 00:26:02,430
See ya.

315
00:26:05,360 --> 00:26:06,918
Go on, wanna go inside?

316
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:13,799
Did they fix her ear?

317
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:16,315
Nah. The vet was out of town.

318
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:19,469
What?

319
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:21,431
Cal called.

320
00:26:23,360 --> 00:26:25,920
- You gonna go out with him?
- I don't know.

321
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:27,359
I think you should.

322
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:29,596
I don't even know him.

323
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:31,033
He's a complete stranger.

324
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:32,559
Oh, that's right.

325
00:26:33,080 --> 00:26:35,548
You only sleep with complete strangers.

326
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:38,194
Maybe you should just have him
meet you at a motel then.

327
00:26:38,320 --> 00:26:40,231
- It'd save time.
- And money.

328
00:26:40,360 --> 00:26:42,555
Courting can be
pretty expensive these days.

329
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:47,475
"Courting." Time for you
to cut back on the Andy Griffith.

330
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:51,158
- You are such a chicken shit.
- I am not.

331
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:54,992
I just felt sorry
for your Ionely ass staying home.

332
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:03,235
You didn't tell me he had T-tops.

333
00:27:04,280 --> 00:27:05,508
Oh, excuse me.

334
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:09,469
I'm Kim.

335
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:11,477
Kim? Cal. Cal Percell.

336
00:27:11,600 --> 00:27:13,113
- Hi.
- Hi.

337
00:27:39,040 --> 00:27:39,950
Oh, no!

338
00:27:44,560 --> 00:27:45,629
Yeah, what can I get you?

339
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:47,716
- I got it, I got it.
- Let me get this round.

340
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:48,915
You got the last one.

341
00:27:49,080 --> 00:27:52,959
I asked you on a date.
Let me take care of this. Thank you.

342
00:28:00,360 --> 00:28:02,032
- Thank you, Cal.
- Sure.

343
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:17,479
Excuse me. Ma'am?

344
00:28:18,120 --> 00:28:19,712
Would you like to dance?

345
00:28:20,760 --> 00:28:21,670
Okay.

346
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:38,435
Well, to our date.

347
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:41,799
If you'll let me.

348
00:28:45,960 --> 00:28:48,155
Have you decided what you're
going to do with that old jukebox?

349
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:49,389
Not yet.

350
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:56,994
- How come you like old music so much?
- I don't know.

351
00:28:57,120 --> 00:28:58,269
Have you always?

352
00:28:58,400 --> 00:29:00,595
I liked nursery rhymes for a while.

353
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:08,236
My dad used to play guitar for me
when I was little,

354
00:29:08,360 --> 00:29:11,557
and he loves all the old music,
so that's probably why.

355
00:29:13,600 --> 00:29:14,715
Was he any good?

356
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:16,273
Hell, what'd I know?
I was eight.

357
00:29:17,840 --> 00:29:19,956
- Well, if you liked it...
- I reckon.

358
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:23,630
He had a band when he was younger,

359
00:29:23,760 --> 00:29:25,478
and they played
in all the bars and stuff around here.

360
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:26,629
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

361
00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:29,909
- But there is one problem.
- What's that?

362
00:29:30,720 --> 00:29:32,199
He's kind of shy,

363
00:29:32,280 --> 00:29:35,477
and my mom says he'd have to be
shit-faced to play in public,

364
00:29:35,600 --> 00:29:38,831
or else he'd make
somebody else stand on stage

365
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:41,070
with a guitar
that wasn't plugged in.

366
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:43,395
But he'd still be playing?

367
00:29:43,480 --> 00:29:45,471
Yeah, behind a curtain or something.

368
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:48,031
- Yeah, I'd say that's shy.
- Yeah.

369
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:53,519
He still play for you?

370
00:29:55,600 --> 00:29:57,079
I gotta pee.

371
00:29:57,920 --> 00:29:59,911
You want Kim to go with you?

372
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:13,952
Three shots of Jack, please.

373
00:30:39,440 --> 00:30:42,000
- Is Kim still dancing?
- Uh, yeah.

374
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:43,879
You wanna?

375
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:46,995
Sure.

376
00:30:47,760 --> 00:30:50,672
- You know how?
- I took cotillion.

377
00:31:40,960 --> 00:31:42,678
Don't sleep with him.

378
00:31:42,800 --> 00:31:44,518
Feed Bessie. Whoa!

379
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:46,669
Oops.

380
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:48,119
You all right, hon?

381
00:31:48,840 --> 00:31:50,239
Ohh...

382
00:32:10,640 --> 00:32:12,278
This is nice.

383
00:32:12,920 --> 00:32:15,753
- Who lives in the front house?
- My aunt and uncle.

384
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:19,998
They were kind enough
to let me stay here till I get my own place.

385
00:32:23,400 --> 00:32:25,470
There's a light here somewhere.

386
00:32:25,600 --> 00:32:26,715
There we are.

387
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:30,033
Got any beer?

388
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:31,388
Uh, yeah.

389
00:32:33,720 --> 00:32:37,076
- Is that your mom?
- Oh, that's my Aunt Wanda.

390
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:39,274
Looks like a spitfire.

391
00:32:40,800 --> 00:32:43,109
- Your uncle?
- Carl.

392
00:32:43,560 --> 00:32:45,790
- They still married?
- 35 years.

393
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:47,194
Shit, really?

394
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:49,512
Are they happy?

395
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:51,514
Seem to be.

396
00:32:54,880 --> 00:32:56,438
What about your parents?

397
00:32:57,160 --> 00:32:59,754
Divorced when I was ten. Yours?

398
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:01,359
Mm-hmm, yeah.

399
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:04,795
My dad had trouble
with the whole being faithful thing.

400
00:33:05,920 --> 00:33:07,717
That woman at the bar...

401
00:33:09,680 --> 00:33:11,033
She wasn't the first.

402
00:33:12,760 --> 00:33:14,716
How many asses
you gonna kick, girl?

403
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:25,831
Whoa. Whoa.

404
00:33:25,960 --> 00:33:27,951
When was the last time
you kissed someone sober?

405
00:33:32,440 --> 00:33:33,555
Huh?

406
00:33:34,800 --> 00:33:36,756
Johnny Patterson.

407
00:33:37,480 --> 00:33:39,357
Skating rink, back corner.

408
00:33:42,760 --> 00:33:44,193
Wasn't any good, though.

409
00:33:45,320 --> 00:33:47,151
Old Johnny had a hard tongue.

410
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:51,397
Why don't I give you a hand?

411
00:33:58,920 --> 00:34:00,876
You have a skating rink
where you grew up?

412
00:34:01,800 --> 00:34:02,915
Yeah.

413
00:34:03,560 --> 00:34:05,551
Yeah. And, uh...

414
00:34:06,600 --> 00:34:08,352
I could skate backwards.

415
00:35:35,720 --> 00:35:36,630
What are you doing?

416
00:35:38,040 --> 00:35:39,439
I've gotta go.

417
00:35:39,560 --> 00:35:42,028
What time is it?

418
00:35:46,200 --> 00:35:48,395
Well, how are you planning
on getting home?

419
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:51,035
A taxi?

420
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:55,152
Jesus, Lucy, I'll take you.

421
00:36:09,120 --> 00:36:11,475
- Well, thanks for the ride.
- Any time.

422
00:36:13,600 --> 00:36:15,591
Kim's home, so the door is unlocked.

423
00:36:19,520 --> 00:36:21,192
Just get out of the car, Lucy.

424
00:36:46,120 --> 00:36:47,599
Wanna go outside? Come on.

425
00:36:48,520 --> 00:36:50,192
Come on, Bessie, go outside.

426
00:37:03,920 --> 00:37:05,399
- Did you have fun?
- Oh!

427
00:37:07,160 --> 00:37:08,832
Scare me half to death.

428
00:37:10,600 --> 00:37:12,352
You're home awfully early.

429
00:37:13,720 --> 00:37:16,792
What were we supposed to do, sit around
and drink coffee and pretend we're in love?

430
00:37:18,280 --> 00:37:20,316
How aboutjust sit around and drink coffee?

431
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:23,793
He didn't have any.

432
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:27,992
Anything happen with you and that guy?

433
00:37:28,120 --> 00:37:29,235
No.

434
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:30,913
You give him your number?

435
00:37:33,520 --> 00:37:35,351
Oh, Jesus, Kim, you didn't.

436
00:37:35,480 --> 00:37:36,595
So what if I did?

437
00:37:36,720 --> 00:37:38,438
Well, are you just stupid?

438
00:37:39,880 --> 00:37:42,110
I mean, my God,
don't you ever get tired

439
00:37:42,240 --> 00:37:45,152
of sitting around
waiting for some jackass to call?

440
00:37:45,280 --> 00:37:47,157
Don't you ever get tired of not?

441
00:38:00,400 --> 00:38:02,550
What do you got against
getting to know these guys?

442
00:38:02,680 --> 00:38:04,238
I thought we got to know each other.

443
00:38:04,320 --> 00:38:06,151
Okay, a little better.

444
00:38:07,880 --> 00:38:09,996
I mean, God, Lucy,
don't you ever meet someone

445
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:12,509
and wonder what they looked like
when they were little?

446
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:14,511
Or what their middle name is?

447
00:38:15,600 --> 00:38:17,556
You know, stupid stuff like that.

448
00:38:22,480 --> 00:38:24,311
Do you think he'll call you again?

449
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:31,671
- Call him.
- I can't.

450
00:38:34,080 --> 00:38:35,513
Why don't you go back over there?

451
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:38,148
Because, Kim,
I wouldn't know what to say.

452
00:38:40,240 --> 00:38:41,150
Well...

453
00:38:41,800 --> 00:38:46,078
He left about ten feet of rubber, so...

454
00:38:47,520 --> 00:38:49,590
I'm guessing "sorry"
might be a good place to start.

455
00:38:53,160 --> 00:38:55,879
Do you know how long it's been
since I kissed somebody sober?

456
00:39:41,280 --> 00:39:42,633
You forget something?

457
00:39:44,480 --> 00:39:47,233
No. I brought you the paper.

458
00:39:47,960 --> 00:39:49,678
There might be places to rent.

459
00:39:53,440 --> 00:39:54,634
Come on in.

460
00:40:04,600 --> 00:40:07,512
You want something to drink?
There's not much.

461
00:40:07,680 --> 00:40:09,875
- Cold beer, maybe a soda?
- No, I'm fine.

462
00:40:14,440 --> 00:40:18,194
You kind of caught me in the middle
of gluing this damn thing together.

463
00:40:18,680 --> 00:40:20,033
What is it?

464
00:40:22,440 --> 00:40:26,638
It's a '71 Boss Mustang
with a 351 Windsor.

465
00:40:28,880 --> 00:40:30,108
It's an engine.

466
00:40:34,200 --> 00:40:35,553
What's this?

467
00:40:35,720 --> 00:40:37,199
It's a passenger seat.

468
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:39,590
You wanna paint it?

469
00:40:39,680 --> 00:40:40,715
Can I?

470
00:40:41,960 --> 00:40:42,870
Sure.

471
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:48,189
No, you can't paint it blue.

472
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:49,594
It has to be black.

473
00:40:49,720 --> 00:40:50,994
How come?

474
00:40:51,120 --> 00:40:53,076
'Cause blue wasn't an option.

475
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:54,195
How do you mean?

476
00:40:54,320 --> 00:40:58,518
I mean you had three colors
from the manufacturer for your interior

477
00:40:58,640 --> 00:41:00,756
when you bought this car.

478
00:41:00,880 --> 00:41:01,676
Black,

479
00:41:01,800 --> 00:41:03,358
red,

480
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:04,515
green.

481
00:41:05,280 --> 00:41:07,555
Well, you're not the manufacturer
and this isn't a real car.

482
00:41:07,720 --> 00:41:08,869
No, it's not.

483
00:41:09,040 --> 00:41:11,952
It's a model.
A model of a real car.

484
00:41:12,120 --> 00:41:13,917
Well, what if somebody really liked blue

485
00:41:14,040 --> 00:41:16,076
and they had a lot of money
and they paid the manufacturer extra?

486
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:17,838
You wanna paint it or not?

487
00:41:17,920 --> 00:41:19,876
Either you paint it black,

488
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:22,434
or go down to the store
and we'll get your very own car.

489
00:41:22,560 --> 00:41:24,437
And you can paint it any color you like.

490
00:41:24,560 --> 00:41:25,879
Black it is.

491
00:41:30,640 --> 00:41:31,959
You know how to paint?

492
00:41:33,360 --> 00:41:37,273
Okay. Don't get any on your fingers.
It's really hard to get off.

493
00:41:41,520 --> 00:41:42,589
Not too thick.

494
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:46,194
You done a lot of these?

495
00:41:46,320 --> 00:41:47,799
Quite a few.

496
00:41:50,640 --> 00:41:51,959
Can I ask a question?

497
00:41:52,080 --> 00:41:53,354
What's that?

498
00:41:54,560 --> 00:41:57,836
It's already black plastic.
How come I have to paint it black?

499
00:41:59,520 --> 00:42:01,909
You know what?
I just remembered why I do this alone.

500
00:42:20,880 --> 00:42:22,438
You wanna go for a drive?

501
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:36,594
Caught a couple of frogs out here
not too long ago.

502
00:42:36,680 --> 00:42:38,511
- Frogs?
- Big ones.

503
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:41,635
- How?
